<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09162</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT STRENGTHENING THE FIRE CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES, REPEALING REPUBLIC ACT 9514 (FIRE CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES OF 2008) AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to clarify the respective authorities and jurisdictions of the BFP, PEZA and other similar entities, 
with respect to the administration and enforcement of the Fire Code in economic zones; harmonize the assessment and collection of Fire Code fees to the assessment and collection made by the LGUs for construction-related permits and business permits.

Aims to expand the utilization of the Fire Code collections; and provide stringent penalties for every acts that tend to compromise fire safety that endangers the lives and limbs as well as properties of the Filipinos.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-03-11</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON PUBLIC ORDER AND SAFETY ON 2019-05-20</td></tr></table>